snippet: Mr. Childers fell in with the Warhol crowd in the late 1960s, capturing images of artists, drag queens, punk musicians and other late-night characters.
abstract: Leee Black Childers, whose photographs of denizens of late-night downtown life told inside story of vibrant musical era in New York City and elsewhere, dies at age 68.
lead_paragraph: Mr. Childers fell in with the Warhol crowd in the late 1960s, capturing images of artists, drag queens, punk musicians and other late-night characters.

headline.main: Leee Black Childers, Portraitist of a Downtown Demimonde, Dies at 68
headline.print_headline: Leee Black Childers, 68, Downtown Portraitist, Dies
